The paper discusses the development of an interactive proof assistant for Euler diagrams, which involves the use of automated reasoning and tactics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on the interaction between the user and the system, which suggests that it may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the construction and analysis of diagrams, which suggests that it may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
